==English==

===Etymology===
From the prefix ''[[oct-]]'' (''eight'') + ''[[-illion]]'' (from [[million]]); [[ie]] the eighth [[power]] of a million, 10<sup>48</sup>.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ɒkˈtɪl.iː.ən/}}, {{SAMPA|/Qk"tIl.i:.@n/}}
*: {{rhymes|ɪljən}}
* {{hyphenation|oct|il|li|on, oc|til|li|on}}

===Cardinal number===
'''octillion'''

# (''US; modern British & Australian, [[w:Long and short scales|short scale]]'') A [[thousand]] [[trillion]] [[trillion]], a [[billion]] [[billion]] [[billion]]: 1 followed by 27 zeros, 10<sup>27</sup>.
# (''dated British & Australian, [[w:Long and short scales|long scale]]'') A [[quadrillion]] [[quintillion]]: 1 followed by 48 zeros, 10<sup>48</sup>.

* ''Western (Arabic) Numeral'' '''octillion''', '''10<sup>27</sup>''' [[w:Long and short scales|short scale]], '''10<sup>48</sup>''' [[w:Long and short scales|long scale]]
